# Mobile UI baseline

Design and verify mobile layouts against a **360px-wide viewport** (common Android minimum for modern apps).

## Viewport assumptions

- **Primary test width**: 360px (`100vw` on a typical small phone)
- **Optional sanity check**: 320px (legacy minimum; do not optimize exclusively for this)
- **Common widths to spot-check**: 375px, 390px (iPhone)

## CSS conventions

- Prefer `100vw` (not `%` of `.app`) for `position: fixed` overlays (toast, modals).
- Side inset: **12px per side** (`calc(100vw - 24px)`) unless a component needs more margin.
- Use `width: fit-content` + `max-width: min(calc(100vw - 24px), 360px)` for compact floating UI (toasts).
- Reset global `button` padding on icon-only controls (e.g. `.toast-close { padding: 0; }`).

## When changing UI

- Confirm layout at **360px** before calling mobile work done.
- Avoid forcing full viewport width on short text unless intentional.
- Prefer slightly smaller type (13px) over squeezing with excessive padding when text wraps on small screens.
